target: input
validations:
  - name: input_state_machine
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify the input module implements a state machine with modes: idle, selecting,
        building, dragging. Transitions must follow: idle->building (via build button or
        number key), idle->selecting (via clicking an entity), idle->dragging (via
        middle-mouse-down), building->idle (via Escape, right-click, or successful
        placement), selecting->idle (via Escape or clicking empty space),
        dragging->idle (via mouse-up). Invalid mode transitions must not occur.

  - name: coordinate_translation
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that mouse event coordinates are correctly translated from screen space
        to tile space. The translation must account for: (1) the canvas CSS scaling
        (getBoundingClientRect ratio), (2) the camera offset, (3) the HUD bar height
        offset. A click at screen pixel (x, y) must map to tile
        floor((x + camera.x) / TILE_SIZE), floor((y - HUD_HEIGHT + camera.y) / TILE_SIZE).
        Clicks in the HUD or sidebar area must not be converted to tile coordinates.

  - name: keyboard_shortcuts
    type: agent_validation
    severity: warning
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify the following keyboard shortcuts are bound and functional: Escape (cancel
        build/selection or toggle pause), Space (toggle pause), 1-5 (select biome types
        for build mode), Arrow keys (pan camera), Tab (cycle sidebar tabs). Each shortcut
        must call preventDefault() on the event to avoid browser default behavior. Shortcuts
        must only function when the game phase is 'playing' or 'paused'.

  - name: tooltip_hover
    type: agent_validation
    severity: warning
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that hovering over an entity for a brief period displays a tooltip with
        relevant information. For animals: species name, happiness, hunger, health. For
        enclosures: biome type, level, animal count/capacity, condition percentage. The
        tooltip must disappear when the mouse moves away from the entity.

  - name: right_click_context_menu
    type: agent_validation
    severity: warning
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that right-clicking on an entity opens a context menu with relevant actions.
        For enclosures: repair, upgrade, demolish. For animals: view info, move. The
        browser's default context menu must be suppressed (preventDefault on contextmenu
        event). Right-clicking in build mode must cancel build mode instead of opening a
        context menu.
